<!-- 01 INTRO -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">01, About this service</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Asko dishwasher service is roughly 80% of every Asko call we run in LA — and the diagnostic tree is genuinely brand-specific.</h2>

    <p>Asko's signature US product is the 82-liter deep-tub dishwasher (the D5, D8, and DBI Pro XL series), and that's the service category we run most across our 5-county SoCal territory by a wide margin. Roughly four out of every five Asko calls we go on are dishwasher work — drain pump failure on the year 5-7 D-series cohort, Aqua Secure leak-detection sensor diagnostics where the trigger is often the sensor itself rather than an actual leak, spray arm bearing wear from the deep-tub volume cycling more water than industry-standard 50-60L tubs do. The remaining 20% splits across the W-series front-load washers (door boot seal pattern on the 2014-2018 W40 cohort, drum bearing service at year 10-12 when the 20-year drum warranty math pays off) and T-series dryers (electric and heat-pump variants). The page covers all three categories but leads with dishwasher service because that's what most Asko owners in LA call us about.</p>

    <p>Asko Appliances was founded in Vara, Sweden, in 1950 by Karl-Erik Andersson, and the Swedish engineering identity — designed for 20-year service life, marine-coastal-climate resilience, deep-tub dishwasher architecture that other brands don't bother with — has stayed intact across the brand's history. Even after the 2018 acquisition by Hisense (the Chinese appliance group that now owns the parent corporation), the engineering, parts numbering, and product specifications continued as they were. We service Asko regularly across the 5-county area, and the owner profile is consistent: West Hollywood, Santa Monica, Venice, Malibu, Newport Beach properties where the homeowner specifically chose Asko over Bosch or Miele because the longevity story resonated. Coastal humidity is part of that fit — Swedish engineering for North Sea climate translates well to Pacific marine layer.</p>

    <p>Two Asko-specific realities shape every service call we run. First, <strong>Asko's US product surface is narrow — laundry and dishwashing only</strong>. Dishwashers (D-series), front-load washers (W-series), and dryers (T-series). No ovens, refrigerators, cooktops, or microwaves under the Asko brand in the US market. Service companies that advertise full Asko kitchen suite repair are confused — Hisense's other brand products are distinct from Asko and use different parts. Second, <strong>Asko dishwashers are built around an 82-liter deep tub</strong>, substantially larger than the industry-standard 50-60L tubs other brands use. The deep-tub architecture changes the spray arm pattern, the drain pump duty cycle, and the wash-cycle algorithm — service diagnosis on an Asko dishwasher follows a different tree than a Bosch or KitchenAid even when the symptom looks similar. Our techs work the Asko-specific service tree directly; competitors who don't service the brand often quote the wrong parts.</p>

    <p>This page covers Asko repair across the full US lineup — dishwashers (the bulk of the work), washers, dryers. Every Asko service call gets a $89 residential diagnostic (applied toward the repair when work is approved), OEM Asko parts via Asko USA distribution, and an honest written quote with parts lead-time disclosed before any work begins.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 02 DISHWASHERS -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">02, Asko dishwasher repair</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">D-series 82L deep-tub architecture and Aqua Secure leak detection.</h2>

    <p class="lead">Asko's US dishwasher lineup spans entry-tier D5 models through the Pro XL variants (taller cavity for large pots and pans). The 82-liter deep-tub volume is the brand's defining engineering choice — substantially more wash capacity than industry-standard 50-60L tubs — and it shapes the service tree distinctively.</p>

    <div class="callout-box">
      <h3>Aqua Secure leak detection sensor trip vs actual leak — most-misdiagnosed Asko service call</h3>
      <p>The Aqua Secure system is a leak-detection sensor in the base pan beneath the dishwasher tub. When water presence is detected, the system shuts off the drain pump and the water inlet valve as a safety measure. Symptoms when triggered: dishwasher won't drain, sometimes a fault code displayed, no visible water on the kitchen floor. About <strong>20% of "Aqua Secure triggered" calls trace to sensor failure or condensate accumulation around the sensor — not an actual leak.</strong> We test the sensor circuit separately before quoting any leak-related repair. When the sensor itself failed, replacement runs $185-$285; when the trigger was condensate buildup from years of operation, cleaning and re-seating the sensor often resolves the issue at no parts cost. Quoting a tub replacement or door seal job blind without sensor diagnostic produces unnecessary repair scope on this brand.</p>
    </div>

    <p>Beyond the Aqua Secure pattern, Asko dishwasher service tree concentrates on a few high-frequency items:</p>

    <ul class="bullet-list">
      <li><strong>Year 5-7:</strong> Drain pump failure on D5 / D8 series. The most common Asko dishwasher service call we see in LA. The 82L deep-tub volume drives more drain duty than industry-standard tubs, and the pump wears accordingly. Replacement runs $285-$425; we stock the common D-series drain pumps on the truck for same-day completion.</li>
      <li><strong>Year 5-7:</strong> Water inlet valve. Wear pattern tracks the drain pump because both components see proportional cycle counts. $225-$345 replacement.</li>
      <li><strong>Year 6-8:</strong> Spray arm bearing. Larger 82L tub means longer spray arm runs, more bearing wear. $185-$285 replacement.</li>
      <li><strong>Year 8-10:</strong> Control board ($385-$580), heating element ($245-$385), door latch / interlock assembly.</li>
      <li><strong>Year 10+:</strong> Door seal full-perimeter replacement, tub structural service (rare — Asko tubs are stainless and well-built), hinge adjustment if door sag has set in.</li>
    </ul>

    <p>Asko Pro XL variants (taller cavity for the dimension class that fits large stockpots) share the same service tree as the standard D-series; the increased height just means slightly different access geometry during pull-work. The DBI series (built-in panel-ready installations) adds the cabinetry-flush installation discipline — we use protective padding during any pull, verify gap-line consistency at reinstall, and shim the mounting bracket if the panel has shifted.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 03 WASHERS & DRYERS -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">03, Asko washer and dryer repair</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">W-series front-load (20-year drum warranty) and T-series dryers.</h2>

    <p class="lead">Asko washers carry a 20-year drum warranty as a brand commitment — Asko engineered the drum, bearing assembly, and chassis for that lifespan. The W-series front-load washers (W4086, W6764, W2084) anchor the laundry lineup; the T-series dryers (T754, T784, including condenser and heat-pump variants) pair with them.</p>

    <div class="callout-box">
      <h3>2014-2018 W40-series door boot seal pattern (common LA coastal-humidity service item)</h3>
      <p>The W4086 and surrounding W40-series production years between roughly 2014 and 2018 develop a door boot seal failure around year 6 to 7 — accelerated in LA coastal addresses (Santa Monica, Venice, Manhattan Beach, Malibu) where marine-layer humidity sits in the boot crease overnight. Symptoms: water on laundry-room floor after a wash cycle, mildew smell around the door area, occasional E-code related to overflow detection. Door boot replacement is the fix; we stock OEM Asko boots on the truck for the W40 frame dimensions. <strong>$285-$425 typical, same-day.</strong> Worth knowing: the coastal-humidity factor compresses the failure window by about 2 years compared to inland addresses on the same model.</p>
    </div>

    <p>Beyond the door boot pattern, Asko washer service tree tracks the high-end front-load category:</p>

    <ul class="bullet-list">
      <li><strong>Year 4-6:</strong> Drain pump filter clog (front-bottom filter, 10-minute no-parts fix when caught at this stage), water inlet valve replacement ($225-$345), door boot seal (above on the coastal cohort).</li>
      <li><strong>Year 6-9:</strong> Drain pump replacement ($285-$425), suspension shock absorber wear (year 8+).</li>
      <li><strong>Year 8-12:</strong> Drum bearing and seal as a paired set ($585-$880). This is the repair that activates Asko's 20-year drum warranty consideration — and it's where the longevity-engineering math pays off. A $700 bearing-seal job on a Year 10 Asko washer extends service life to year 16-18, vs replacing the unit at year 10 on a mass-market brand. Honest math at diagnostic before authorization.</li>
      <li><strong>Year 10+:</strong> Main control board ($445-$680), door hinge alignment if the boot service didn't fully restore it.</li>
    </ul>

    <p>Asko dryer service is less brand-specific than the dishwashers or washers. Most calls trace to thermal fuse failure from vent blockage (always inspect the full vent path before replacing the fuse — fuse alone will blow again within weeks), heating element burnout at year 8-12 on electric T-series, idler pulley and drum belt wear at year 7-10. The condenser and heat-pump T-series variants add specific service items: heat-pump compressor service on heat-pump models year 8-10 ($580-$880), condenser coil cleaning service (LA dust load), refrigerant charge verification on the heat-pump models (EPA 608 certified for refrigerant work).</p>
  </div>
</section>

