<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">06, Recent repairs</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Asko jobs from across the territory.</h2>

    <p class="lead">Three representative service calls — model, symptom, diagnosis, repair, and cost. Names and addresses omitted; technical scenarios are typical of what we see on Asko service.</p>

    <div class="repair-grid">
      <div class="repair-card">
        <h3>Asko D5436XLS dishwasher, West Hollywood</h3>
        <p><strong>Symptom:</strong> Dishwasher wouldn't drain at end of cycle. Standing water in the tub. Owner had cleaned the drain filter once, error returned within two cycles. Unit was 6 years old.</p>
        <p><strong>Diagnosis:</strong> Filter cleaned again on diagnostic visit, confirmed clean. Tested drain pump amp draw: 30% above spec, classic D5-series year 5-7 drain pump wear pattern. Pump still managing to drain on lighter loads but timing out on full loads. Aqua Secure sensor circuit tested clean — no false trip.</p>
        <p><strong>Repair:</strong> Drain pump replacement with OEM Asko part (in stock on truck). Verified normal drain cycle time on test wash. Confirmed full drainage across three test cycles.</p>
        <p><strong>Cost & time:</strong> $365 total. Same-day, completed on the diagnostic visit in 75 minutes.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="repair-card">
        <h3>Asko W4086C front-load washer, Santa Monica</h3>
        <p><strong>Symptom:</strong> Water on laundry-room floor after every wash. Owner noticed mildew smell around the door over the past month. Unit was 7 years old, in the 2017 production cohort.</p>
        <p><strong>Diagnosis:</strong> Classic 2014-2018 W40-series coastal-humidity door boot seal failure pattern. Lower lip tear at 6-o'clock position; marine-layer condensate had compressed the rubber faster than inland addresses on the same model. Tear visible on inspection. Drum bearing and seal tested separately, both within spec — boot was the isolated failure.</p>
        <p><strong>Repair:</strong> Door boot replacement with OEM Asko part. Cleaned mildew accumulation in the boot crease. Reinstalled, ran test cycle, confirmed no leaks.</p>
        <p><strong>Cost & time:</strong> $365 total. Same-day, 90 minutes on-site.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="repair-card">
        <h3>Asko DBI675 Pro XL dishwasher, Beverly Hills</h3>
        <p><strong>Symptom:</strong> Aqua Secure triggered — dishwasher wouldn't run, displayed leak fault. Owner had inspected under-cabinet, found no visible water. Unit was 5 years old, panel-ready integrated install.</p>
        <p><strong>Diagnosis:</strong> Tested Aqua Secure sensor circuit separately. Sensor itself reading out of spec — false trip from condensate accumulation around the sensor housing. No actual leak. Tub and door seal inspected and confirmed dry. Drain pump and water valve tested clean.</p>
        <p><strong>Repair:</strong> Cleaned sensor housing and re-seated the sensor. Verified clean circuit reading. Ran test cycle, confirmed no fault. Documented sensor condition for the owner's records — likely 3-4 year re-service interval before sensor housing accumulates condensate again.</p>
        <p><strong>Cost & time:</strong> $185 total. Same-day, 60 minutes on-site. Would have been $580-$880 if a leak-related component had been quoted blind without sensor diagnostic first.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
